HEADWORD: Tucan
<hw>Tu*can"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
Mexican pocket gopher (<spn>Geomys Mexicanus</spn>). It resembles the
common pocket gopher of the Western United States, but is larger. Called
also <altname>tugan</altname>, and <altname>tuza</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tucet</ent>⟦br⟧
